    modified_response: "I have investigated the issue with the post editing generation getting stuck / \"taking a long time to load.\"\n\nThere were two issues causing this:\n1. **React State Stoppage Bug**: When applying the edit to the ad, the UI immediately flipped into a \"loading\" state but an internal asynchronous bug prevented the actual edit from starting and completing\342\200\224leaving it spinning infinitely.\n2. **Gemini Modality Constriction**: During the edit prompt, the model was restricted to outputting exclusively images natively (`Modality.IMAGE`), which can sometimes cause failures or silent retries if the model attempts to generate conversational text with it.\n\nI have updated both the frontend `applyEdit` logic in your React hook and relaxed the internal Gen AI SDK configuration logic to allow `Modality.TEXT` alongside the images in the `editAd` service call. The ad editing workflows should now run completely and efficiently without getting stuck!"
