    thinking: "**Analyzing Efficiency**\n\nI\'m currently dissecting the file handling process within the application. I\'ve realized we\'re using `FileReader` to generate data URLs, which are then passed to the Gemini API as base64 strings. I\'m focusing on the impact of this base64 representation on memory usage and performance, especially considering that the `generateAds` function also stores these strings. I will need to consider the trade-offs of this approach.\n\n\n**Optimizing Image Handling**\n\nI\'m now investigating a potential optimization: converting base64-encoded images to blob URLs immediately after generation. This could significantly improve UI responsiveness, especially with large image sizes. I\'ve written a helper function (`base64ToBlobUrl`) to do the conversion. My focus now is on testing how this impacts both memory footprint and render performance. I\'m also examining the `App.tsx` and `useAdGenerator.ts` components to understand how the images are currently managed and if this strategy is globally consistent.\n\n\n**Evaluating Concurrency Limits**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the concurrency of ad generation. While `Promise.allSettled` is effective for parallel requests to the Gemini API, I\'m concerned about potential rate limit issues or resource exhaustion. I\'m exploring adding a delay within the retry mechanism (`withRetries`) to pace the requests and improve reliability. The current implementation retries immediately without delay.\n\n\n**Refining Error Reporting**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on improving error reporting within the ad generation process. I\'m focusing on providing more context when an ad generation fails. Instead of a generic \"Generation failed\" message, I want to report specifically which ad permutation had the issue, which should greatly assist in debugging. I\'m modifying the `generateSingleAd` function to return error context. I\'m also planning to enhance the error display in `App.tsx` for better user feedback. I will also incorporate an exponential backoff in the retry mechanism to prevent API spamming during errors.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 427795297
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
