  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reporting Back Completion**\n\nThe build process completed with \"npm run build\". However, I now understand the instruction to only \"report back.\" Therefore, I\'m providing this update as the only required action. I will now gather my thoughts and generate a detailed report, as requested.\n\n\n**Analyzing Resource Usage**\n\nI\'ve been examining resource management. Creating multiple ad variations in parallel could strain the browser if the payloads are heavy or trigger rate limits, despite the use of `allSettled`. My analysis of `useAdGenerator.ts` reveals robust state handling, though `applyEdit` waits serially for `editAd`, which could be optimized. Also, I noticed that `fileToBase64` processes images without compression; resizing images with a Canvas before Base64 conversion will save bandwidth.\n\nI\'ve been also focusing on error handling.\nI see the newly implemented exponential backoff with jitter in `geminiService.ts`, which is great for handling rate limits. The reporting format isolates standard issues nicely. I am concerned that the error handling in `generateAds` might overwrite more specific errors. The catch statement in `generateAds` which sets `{ status: \'error\', error: \'Batch failed\' }` inside `try...catch`, this can overwrite more specific errors caught in `generateSingleAd` mapping.\n\n\n**Addressing Backend Vulnerability**\n\nI\'m now deeply concerned about the lack of a proper backend. The current static React app using Vite (`type: \"spa\"`) has no server-side component. The critical issue is the API key leak: `vite.config.ts` injects the `GEMINI_API_KEY` into the frontend bundle at build time using Vite `define:`. This makes the key visible in the browser source. Furthermore, deploying this static bundle to Cloud Run will bake in the key used at build, making it unresponsive to Cloud Run environment variable changes at runtime!\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 438099279
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
