  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing the Server**\n\nOkay, I\'m making progress on setting up the server! I\'ve decided to build `server.ts` to integrate Express with Vite. I also need to update `vite.config.ts` to manage API keys properly. Finally, I\'ll modify `package.json` to have the start script run the server file.\n\n\n**Refactoring Service Logic**\n\nOkay, I\'m now in the middle of reorganizing the service layer. It\'s becoming clearer that I need to move the existing Gemini service logic to the server directory, specifically `server/geminiService.ts`. I also realize the need to wrap the `/api/...` calls. I plan to handle the `/api/...` route calls as a direct export from the Gemini server file. Now I\'m preparing the server file. It will import Express and Vite.\n\n\n**Simplifying Imports and Logic**\n\nI\'m now simplifying the import strategy. While exploring Node\'s type stripping, I\'ve decided to keep it straightforward. I\'ll create `server.ts` and `server/gemini.ts`. The former will import from the latter, and I\'ll focus on resolving any ESM pathing issues. This approach maintains simplicity and hopefully circumvents any potential extension-related complications with type stripping. My immediate goal is to ensure a clean import process.\n\n\n**Restructuring Module Imports**\n\nI\'m now revising my import strategy to streamline the process and sidestep potential complications. I\'ve chosen to move the `geminiService` content directly into `server/geminiService.ts`, avoiding any ESM pathing concerns. Then, I plan to rewrite the original `services/geminiService.ts` to make simple `fetch` calls. I\'ve also decided to handle the `generateAds` logic in the client, calling `/api/generateSingleAd` in parallel, or make an endpoint for `/api/generateAds`.\n\n\n**Synchronizing Service Exports**\n\nI\'m now synchronizing export signatures, ensuring parity between `hooks/useAdGenerator.ts` and the updated service. I need to guarantee that the `services/geminiService.ts` API client exports match those used in the hook and `App.tsx`, specifically `generateAds`, `generateSingleAd`, `editAd`, `styleVariations`, `getCopySuggestion`, and `generateLifestyleImage`. I\'m rewriting `services/geminiService.ts` as an API client while simultaneously creating `server.ts`. This ensures no signature errors occur during the transition.\n\n\n**Defining API Client Functions**\n\nI\'m now implementing the API client functions. I\'ve defined the asynchronous `getFileData` helper to convert files to base64, resolving the promise with the MIME type. I\'ve also written the `handleFetch` function, ensuring error handling and returning JSON responses. I\'m focusing on defining `getCopySuggestion`, and I\'m adding `editAd`, which manages base images, prompts, reference images, and aspect ratios to improve image generation.\n\n\n**Finalizing API Client**\n\nI\'ve just added the `generateLifestyleImage` and `generateSingleAd` functions to the API client, using `handleFetch` to streamline network requests. These functions will handle complex parameters like images and ad copy, allowing the client to call endpoints more easily. Now I can complete the setup for client-side ad generation. I\'m focusing on ensuring these functions are properly integrated and testable.\n\n\n**Adjusting Request Limits**\n\nI\'m now implementing the server-side Gemini code. I\'ve increased the Express request limit to manage larger payloads. I\'ve also incorporated the `generateAds` function, but realized I need to restructure the server-side code to include this logic. I plan to use this function to parallelize the requests on the server.\n\n\n**Simplifying the Server**\n\nOkay, I\'ve decided to keep `server.ts` self-contained to avoid import complications. I\'m moving the original Gemini logic directly into it. I\'m removing front-end helper functions, and I will be working on handling environment variables like the API key, but everything else is complete.\n\n\n**Finalizing Server Routes**\n\nI\'m now completing the server-side routes, including `/api/generate-ads`, `/api/generate-lifestyle`, and `/api/generate-single-ad`. I\'m integrating Vite middleware for development and static file serving for production. I\'ve also addressed Express version compatibility to ensure smooth operation across different environments. Now, I\'m verifying the server setup to ensure everything is connected.\n\n\n"
