    modified_response: "I have restructured the application to a full-stack Express + Vite architecture, making it ready and secure for Cloud Run deployment!\n\nHere is a summary of the changes implemented for the architectural upgrade:\n\n1. **Integrated Express Server (`server.ts`)**: Created the main entry point to run an Express server that natively handles your backend logic and serves Vite\'s static static files (`dist`) in the production environment.\n2. **Secured Gemini API Key**: The `@google/genai` logic and API calls have been completely migrated to `server.ts`. This means the `GEMINI_API_KEY` is fully hidden from the client browser and is strictly managed on the backend.\n3. **API Endpoints Created**: \n   - `/api/copy-suggestion`\n   - `/api/edit-ad`\n   - `/api/generate-lifestyle`\n   - `/api/generate-single-ad`\n4. **Client Services Restructured (`services/geminiService.ts`)**: This file has been refactored from performing direct AI API calls to a clean API client that securely dispatches HTTPS requests (`fetch`) to the newly built Express backend.\n5. **Vite & JSON Configuration Modfied**: Updated the `package.json` with standard build scripts (`\"start\": \"node server.ts\"` and `\"dev\": \"tsx server.ts\"`) for backend execution. Also wiped the exposed `API_KEY` defines from `vite.config.ts`.\n6. **Payload Size Extended**: Adjusted Express middleware\'s JSON limits natively (`app.use(express.json({ limit: \'200mb\' }))`) since large image generation payloads (base 64) will be sent down the pipe.\n\nYou can interact with your application directly using the live preview \342\200\223 it\'s running securely behind the newly structured Express server! Everything is well-prepared for seamless deployment via Cloud Run. Let me know if you want to explore further optimizations or add anything else!"
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
